# PolBud Construction Website - Change Log

## 2025-09-22 - Mobile Responsiveness Fixes

**Time:** 15:15 - 16:45 (UTC)
**Objective:** Fix mobile layout issues - overlay problems and hero section height

### Issues Identified
1. "Dachy i Elewacje" hero widget overlapping with infographic widgets below on mobile
2. Hero section not filling full viewport height, leaving white space at bottom
3. Inconsistent z-index management causing layout conflicts

### Changes Implemented

#### 1. Enhanced Mobile Hero Section Height (src/App.css)
- **Lines 662-683:** Implemented layered viewport height fallbacks
  - `height: 100vh` → `calc(100vh - 64px)` → `calc(100dvh - 64px)` → `calc(100svh - 64px)`
  - Added safety minimum heights (500px mobile, 600px tablet)
  - Switched from `min-height` to `height` for reliable viewport coverage
  - Enhanced flexbox layout for better content positioning

#### 2. Systematic Z-Index Management (src/App.css)
- **Lines 123-137:** Added CSS custom properties for z-index hierarchy
  - Navigation: 50, Stats: 15, Cards: 10, Sections: 5
  - Prevents overlay conflicts with maintainable system

#### 3. Improved Section Separation (src/App.css)
- **Lines 698-744:** Enhanced spacing between hero and services sections
  - Mobile: 8rem bottom padding, 3rem top margin
  - Small screens: 9rem bottom padding, 4rem top margin
  - Added gradient background for visual separation

#### 4. Landscape Orientation Support (src/App.css)
- **Lines 747-761:** Added landscape-specific optimizations
  - Reduced padding (4rem) to maximize content space
  - Adjusted stats positioning and hero card padding

#### 5. Stats Container Positioning (src/App.jsx)
- **Line 227:** Added `stats-container-mobile` class for better mobile positioning
- **Line 120:** Removed redundant z-50 class (now handled by CSS)

### Files Modified
- `src/App.css`: Comprehensive mobile responsiveness improvements
- `src/App.jsx`: Minor positioning class updates

### Testing Recommendations
- Verify fixes on mobile devices 320px-768px width
- Test both portrait and landscape orientations  
